  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum number of set bits in the product of 2023 and n. Since 2023 is not a power of 2, the minimum k(n) is at least 1. I will delegate the search for the minimum k(n) by checking small integer values for k(n) and the verification of existence.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Systematically check if there exists a positive integer n such that k(n) = 1, then k(n) = 2, then k(n) = 3, and so on. For each value of k, determine if there is an n such that 2023 * n is a sum of exactly k powers of 2. Specifically, check if 2023 divides 2^a for k=1, then if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for k=2, then if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c for k=3, etc. Provide the smallest k for which such an n exists and the corresponding powers of 2."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Verify the result obtained by helper_1. If helper_1 claims the minimum k(n) is some value K, prove that for all m < K, there is no n such that 2023 * n has exactly m ones in its binary representation. This can be done by checking the divisibility of sums of m powers of 2 by 2023 using modular arithmetic (2^x mod 2023)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the smallest k found by helper_1 and use the proof/verification from helper_2 to confirm that no smaller k is possible, concluding that the minimum k(n) is the value provided."
}

